 :tx/rationale "DAEMON-ARCH-2: Runtime Schema Design. Six new schema attributes for reflexive observation: :runtime/command (String, One) — command name or tool name. :runtime/request-id (String, One) — JSON-RPC request id as string. :runtime/latency-ms (Long, One) — wall clock milliseconds for request processing. :runtime/outcome (String, One) — 'success' or 'error'. :runtime/datom-count (Long, One) — store.len() at request start (for tracking growth). :runtime/cache-hit (Boolean, One) — whether refresh_if_needed() found no new txns (O(1) fast path). These attributes are installed as schema datoms during daemon startup via a runtime schema transaction. They follow C3 (schema-as-data) and are queryable via standard Datalog: [:find ?cmd ?lat :where [?e :runtime/command ?cmd] [?e :runtime/latency-ms ?lat]]. Each command execution creates one runtime entity with all 6 attributes plus :db/ident (:runtime/req-{hash}). Runtime datoms use the same 6 ADR-029 lifecycle attributes as all other knowledge. ADR-DAEMON-003, INV-DAEMON-003."
